# Wasp Compile Verification

After making code changes (new files, edits to `.ts`/`.tsx`/`.wasp`/`.prisma` files), always run `wasp compile` from the `app/` directory to verify there are no TypeScript or Wasp compilation errors.

```bash
cd app && wasp compile
```

- Fix any errors before considering the task complete.
- If compilation fails, read the error output carefully and address each issue before re-running.
